criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1) Allogeneic stem cell transplantation candidates with acute myeloid leukemia. Donor selection was performed as the follows: HLA-matched sibling donor was the first choice for allo-transplantation. If an HLA-matched sibling donor was unavailable, subjects without a suitable closely HLA-matched unrelated donor (URD; >8 of 10 matching HLA-A, B, C, DR, and DQloci and >5 of 6 matching HLA-A, B, and DR loci) after 2 cycles of consolidation were eligible for HLA-haplotype transplantation;
2) Between 6 and 60 years-old; 
3) To be able to provide written informed consent.
